node.text:
Today the @afthunderbirds flew over Front Range communities to honor health care workers, first responders, military members and other essential personnel who are working on the front lines to combat Covid-19. Here is the moment the Thunderbirds flew over downtown Denver this afternoon. It was beautiful!! Did you see the flyover from your house today? Video credit: @9newsdenver

node.text:
@1natvson1 on the main stage this afternoon at @iamjuneteenth music festival 🎶 🎤 Also pictured is @sunsofatliens 💯

#Juneteenth celebrates the liberation of enslaved African-Americans in 1865 for whom freedom was delayed nearly two and a half years after the Emancipation Proclamation was signed. On June 17, 2021, President Joe Biden signed a bill making Juneteenth the eleventh American federal holiday and the first to obtain legal observance as a federal holiday since Martin Luther King Jr. Day was designated in 1983.

In Denver, Juneteenth celebrations began in the early 1950s and eventually grew to be one of the nation's largest celebrations of its kind. The fun continues all weekend with live music, dance, discussion panels, food, street vendors, art installations and more. Five Points neighborhood on Welton St. between 24th and 29th.

📷: @juliana.amann
